Parliament. eNCA/Zaid Harris JOHANNESBURG - You may need a Plan B if you're driving near Parliament on Thursday. Officials say several roads will be closed between 6am and 11pm. The closures are part of the security measures for the State of the Nation Address. The president will deliver his speech at 7pm. WATCH: No pomp and ceremony for Sona 2021 The closures include sections of Roeland and Plein Streets, as well as several other roads close to Parliament. Authorities will also impose a no-fly zone over the Parliamentary precinct. They've warned that drones will not be allowed in the area and also stressed that any demonstrators must follow lockdown regulations. Two areas will be designated for demonstrations and protests. These include a section of the Grand Parade, as well as the Hanover Street parking area. Sona Roads Closure